tapes on how to
think properly, how

00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:46.950 align:middle line:84%
to master your emotions
a little bit more,

00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:48.960 align:middle line:84%
and how to sell
more real estate.

00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:51.450 align:middle line:84%
I said, but I'm going to
charge you $500 for them

00:10:51.450 --> 00:10:52.950 align:middle line:84%
because that's what
I paid for them.

00:10:52.950 --> 00:10:56.160 align:middle line:84%
And I've been listening to
them every day for 30 minutes

00:10:56.160 --> 00:11:00.690 align:middle line:84%
to an hour a day like my
mentors taught me to listen to.

00:11:00.690 --> 00:11:03.000 align:middle line:90%
And he was like, what? $500?

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:03.930 align:middle line:90%
Are you crazy?

00:11:03.930 --> 00:11:07.710 align:middle line:84%
I said, listen, it's helped
me make a lot of money

00:11:07.710 --> 00:11:10.800 align:middle line:84%
investing in real estate, as
well as selling real estate.

00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:13.920 align:middle line:84%
So if you want them,
I'll sell them to you,

00:11:13.920 --> 00:11:16.750 align:middle line:84%
and I'll buy them back
from you when I come back.

00:11:16.750 --> 00:11:19.690 align:middle line:90%
So he gave me $500 back in 1982.

00:11:19.690 --> 00:11:22.170 align:middle line:90%
And I gave him my cassettes.

00:11:22.170 --> 00:11:23.820 align:middle line:84%
And he started to
listen to them.

00:11:23.820 --> 00:11:29.820 align:middle line:84%
And by the time I came back,
it was November of 1983,

00:11:29.820 --> 00:11:34.140 align:middle line:84%
14 months later, he
had made six figures,

00:11:34.140 --> 00:11:36.930 align:middle line:90%
over $100,000 in real estate.

00:11:36.930 --> 00:11:40.300 align:middle line:84%
And when I asked
him, what happened?

00:11:40.300 --> 00:11:43.650 align:middle line:84%
He says, well, I
paid you $500, and I

00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:45.510 align:middle line:84%
started listening
to those cassettes

00:11:45.510 --> 00:11:48.420 align:middle line:84%
on my way to work and
back home every day

00:11:48.420 --> 00:11:50.910 align:middle line:84%
for 30 minutes to
45 minutes a day.

00:11:50.910 --> 00:11:53.700 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I really
don't know what happened,

00:11:53.700 --> 00:11:55.690 align:middle line:84%
but I started to
think differently.

00:11:55.690 --> 00:11:58.350 align:middle line:90%
I started to feel differently.

00:11:58.350 --> 00:12:01.170 align:middle line:84%
And I started selling
more real estate.

00:12:01.170 --> 00:12:05.820 align:middle line:84%
And I remember saying, well,
I want those cassettes back.

00:12:05.820 --> 00:12:08.700 align:middle line:84%
>> And when I hit a
barrier on my journey,

00:12:08.700 --> 00:12:10.920 align:middle line:90%
it's always a belief barrier.

00:12:10.920 --> 00:12:15.480 align:middle line:84%
It's never anything other
than a belief barrier.

00:12:15.480 --> 00:12:18.060 align:middle line:84%
It's never anybody
else's fault. It's

00:12:18.060 --> 00:12:21.360 align:middle line:84%
never that I'm a victim
of my circumstances.

00:12:21.360 --> 00:12:27.690 align:middle line:84%
It's never that there's nothing
I could have done or said

00:12:27.690 --> 00:12:30.210 align:middle line:90%
or thought differently.

00:12:30.210 --> 00:12:34.260 align:middle line:84%
It's always a function
of how I am in the world

00:12:34.260 --> 00:12:38.640 align:middle line:90%
and what I believe to be true.

00:12:38.640 --> 00:12:40.590 align:middle line:90%
And that is what I meet.

00:12:40.590 --> 00:12:45.660 align:middle line:84%
I meet my truth, whatever
it is at the time.

00:12:45.660 --> 00:12:50.080 align:middle line:84%
It's reflected back
to me in the world.

00:12:50.080 --> 00:12:53.190 align:middle line:84%
And if I don't like the truth
that's being reflected back

00:12:53.190 --> 00:12:56.130 align:middle line:84%
to me, then the place
to put my effort

00:12:56.130 --> 00:12:58.530 align:middle line:84%
is not to try and
change the world.

00:12:58.530 --> 00:13:02.820 align:middle line:84%
The place to put my effort
is to change what I believe,

00:13:02.820 --> 00:13:06.540 align:middle line:84%
and the world that
I see will change.

00:13:06.540 --> 00:13:13.680 align:middle line:84%
>> I could recite those audio
cassettes verbatim today from

00:13:13.680 --> 00:13:19.500 align:middle line:84%
what I listened to 31
years ago, verbatim.

00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:24.720 align:middle line:84%
I could recite every script,
every question, every answer

00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:26.370 align:middle line:90%
because I did it religiously.

00:13:26.370 --> 00:13:31.650 align:middle line:84%
I did it as a very,
very serious practice.

00:13:31.650 --> 00:13:34.620 align:middle line:84%
And I was told back
then that repetition

00:13:34.620 --> 00:13:36.630 align:middle line:84%
was the mother of
skill, and repetition

00:13:36.630 --> 00:13:41.430 align:middle line:84%
was the mother of learning
and that you had to practice

00:13:41.430 --> 00:13:43.270 align:middle line:90%
over and over and over again.

00:13:43.270 --> 00:13:46.550 align:middle line:84%
One time we were training the
wealthy-minded in Australia.

00:13:46.550 --> 00:13:48.127 align:middle line:84%
And when we were
there, we decided

00:13:48.127 --> 00:13:49.710 align:middle line:84%
if we were going to
go that far, we're

00:13:49.710 --> 00:13:52.290 align:middle line:84%
going to go to Cairns and
the Great Barrier Reef.

00:13:52.290 --> 00:13:54.143 align:middle line:90%
And we went and visited that.

00:13:54.143 --> 00:13:56.310 align:middle line:84%
And then, we're going on
to Sydney for the training.

00:13:56.310 --> 00:13:59.400 align:middle line:84%
And so we called a taxi
to take us from our hotel

00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:00.870 align:middle line:90%
to the airport.

00:14:00.870 --> 00:14:02.820 align:middle line:90%
And this fellow picks us up.

00:14:02.820 --> 00:14:05.580 align:middle line:84%
And he's driving a
little bit, and he said,

00:14:05.580 --> 00:14:08.700 align:middle line:84%
I can tell that you're from
America by your accent.

00:14:08.700 --> 00:14:10.140 align:middle line:90%
And he said, you're so lucky.

00:14:10.140 --> 00:14:13.020 align:middle line:84%
He said, you can never get
ahead in the Australian economy.

00:14:13.020 --> 00:14:14.658 align:middle line:90%
It's utterly impossible.

00:14:14.658 --> 00:14:16.200 align:middle line:84%
He went on to tell
us how horrible it

00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:18.262 align:middle line:90%
was and impossible it was.

00:14:18.262 --> 00:14:19.720 align:middle line:84%
And he said, so
what have you done?

00:14:19.720 --> 00:14:21.977 align:middle line:84%
And we said, well, we went
to the Great Barrier Reef,

00:14:21.977 --> 00:14:23.560 align:middle line:84%
and we went up to
this wonderful beach

00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:25.590 align:middle line:90%
place called Port Douglas.

00:14:25.590 --> 00:14:27.302 align:middle line:90%
And he said Port Douglas?

00:14:27.302 --> 00:14:28.510 align:middle line:90%
I'd never go to Port Douglas.

00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:29.620 align:middle line:90%
That's for rich people.

00:14:29.620 --> 00:14:33.160 align:middle line:84%
And he went on and on about how
impossible it was in Australia

00:14:33.160 --> 00:14:34.420 align:middle line:90%
to ever get ahead.

00:14:34.420 --> 00:14:38.500 align:middle line:84%
So we got to the airport,
got on an airplane,

00:14:38.500 --> 00:14:40.210 align:middle line:84%
flew to Sydney
where we were going

00:14:40.210 --> 00:14:43.990 align:middle line:84%
to be driven to our hotel,
and a taxi driver drives up.

00:14:43.990 --> 00:14:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And he jumps out,
and he goes, hello.

00:14:46.090 --> 00:14:47.710 align:middle line:84%
And he says, where
are you going?

00:14:47.710 --> 00:14:49.240 align:middle line:90%
And we said The Gazebo Hotel.

00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:51.970 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well,
I'll tell you what.

00:14:51.970 --> 00:14:54.970 align:middle line:84%
I can drive you a couple of
streets off of how I normally

00:14:54.970 --> 00:14:57.370 align:middle line:84%
go, and I'll show you a
great view of Sydney Harbor

00:14:57.370 --> 00:14:59.177 align:middle line:90%
that you'll never see otherwise.

00:14:59.177 --> 00:15:00.010 align:middle line:90%
Would you like that?

00:15:00.010 --> 00:15:01.593 align:middle line:84%
He said, I won't
even charge you more.

00:15:01.593 --> 00:15:04.290 align:middle line:84%
We said, well, sure,
that'd be great.

00:15:04.290 --> 00:15:05.410 align:middle line:90%
He's talking to us.

00:15:05.410 --> 00:15:07.570 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, I'm
going to miss this job.

00:15:07.570 --> 00:15:09.140 align:middle line:90%
And we said, miss this job?

00:15:09.140 --> 00:15:09.940 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:15:09.940 --> 00:15:12.285 align:middle line:84%
He said, well, he said, my
wife and I are retiring.

00:15:12.285 --> 00:15:14.410 align:middle line:84%
And we said, oh, well, so
what are you going to do?

00:15:14.410 --> 00:15:15.800 align:middle line:84%
He said, we're
retiring up north.

00:15:15.800 --> 00:15:17.530 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, north,
what's up there?

00:15:17.530 --> 00:15:18.652 align:middle line:90%
Brisbane, Gold Coast.

00:15:18.652 --> 00:15:20.110 align:middle line:84%
I said, is that
where you're going?

00:15:20.110 --> 00:15:23.890 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh no, we're
going much further north.

00:15:23.890 --> 00:15:27.010 align:middle line:90%
We're retiring in Port Douglas.

00:15:27.010 --> 00:15:30.130 align:middle line:84%
And it was a story that's
always really stuck with me

00:15:30.130 --> 00:15:34.180 align:middle line:84%
because it's the same
economy, the same job, and one

00:15:34.180 --> 00:15:37.390 align:middle line:84%
person had a belief system
that enabled him to create

00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:40.030 align:middle line:84%
the life he wanted, and the
other one was stuck in his rut.

00:15:40.030 --> 00:15:43.360 align:middle line:84%
>> It wasn't something
that I was born with.

00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:46.540 align:middle line:90%
It was a skill that I learned.

00:15:46.540 --> 00:15:51.880 align:middle line:84%
And as I've studied other people
in every area of their life--

00:15:51.880 --> 00:15:53.950 align:middle line:84%
health, wealth, relationships,
career, business,

00:15:53.950 --> 00:15:55.960 align:middle line:90%
spiritual growth--

00:15:55.960 --> 00:15:59.410 align:middle line:84%
everybody goes through the ebb
and flow of life-- everybody.

00:15:59.410 --> 00:16:02.980 align:middle line:84%
There's no human being
that's impervious to it.

00:16:02.980 --> 00:16:05.440 align:middle line:84%
I don't care if
you're a monk that

00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:09.400 align:middle line:84%
is meditating for eight
hours a day in Dharamshala.

00:16:09.400 --> 00:16:12.130 align:middle line:84%
You go through highs
and lows, ups and downs.

00:16:12.130 --> 00:16:15.820 align:middle line:84%
And there are moments that
thoughts bring you down.

00:16:15.820 --> 00:16:19.960 align:middle line:84%
And you can develop the
skill of observation.

00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:23.350 align:middle line:84%
You can develop the
skill of nonjudgment.

00:16:23.350 --> 00:16:26.440 align:middle line:84%
You can develop the
skill of awareness.

00:16:26.440 --> 00:16:31.660 align:middle line:84%
You can develop the skill of
allowing things to happen.

00:16:31.660 --> 00:16:35.710 align:middle line:84%
>> I went through a process
of actively and consciously

00:16:35.710 --> 00:16:37.720 align:middle line:90%
reprogramming my beliefs.

00:16:37.720 --> 00:16:42.310 align:middle line:84%
I used very specific steps that
I had learned and developed

00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:44.830 align:middle line:84%
through my process to
reprogram my beliefs.

00:16:44.830 --> 00:16:49.600 align:middle line:84%
I saw my beliefs as either
an asset or a liability.

00:16:49.600 --> 00:16:51.340 align:middle line:84%
I didn't care if they
were real or not.

00:16:51.340 --> 00:16:53.560 align:middle line:84%
I just cared if they were
an asset or a liability.

00:16:53.560 --> 00:16:56.650 align:middle line:84%
I just saw that the ones that
would benefit me were assets.

00:16:56.650 --> 00:16:58.058 align:middle line:90%
And I instilled them.

00:16:58.058 --> 00:17:00.100 align:middle line:84%
And the ones that were
liabilities, I got rid of.

00:17:00.100 --> 00:17:03.270 align:middle line:84%
And I did that process
on a daily basis

00:17:03.270 --> 00:17:05.770 align:middle line:84%
through affirmations
and visualizations

00:17:05.770 --> 00:17:07.420 align:middle line:90%
and mental training.

00:17:07.420 --> 00:17:11.200 align:middle line:84%
I absolutely recreated my
belief system, step-by-step,

00:17:11.200 --> 00:17:13.560 align:middle line:84%
brick-by-brick, no
question about it.

00:17:13.560 --> 00:17:17.204 align:middle line:84%
>> The good news is the
brain can change at any time.

00:17:17.204 --> 00:17:18.579 align:middle line:84%
So if you jump
out of that groove

00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:21.819 align:middle line:84%
and if you challenge those
old beliefs, old patterns,

00:17:21.819 --> 00:17:24.400 align:middle line:84%
old environments, and you
get into new environments,

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:25.700 align:middle line:90%
you can change.

00:17:25.700 --> 00:17:30.239 align:middle line:84%
So the past is an advisor,
not a determinant.

00:17:30.239 --> 00:17:37.366 align:middle line:90%